{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place sugar and orange peelings in mixing bowl then grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides and base of mixing bowl with spatula then grind again <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Add flour and butter then mix <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/4 times<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add currants, egg yolk and 1 Tbsp orange juice then mix <b>8 sec\/\/speed 4<b>. Tip out and bring together into a ball. Wrap in cling film and allow to rest in fridge for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180°C and line two baking trays with baking paper.","Divide rested dough in half and roll out each piece on a lightly floured surface until 3-4 mm thick. Cut out rounds using a fluted cookie cutter (Ø 6 cm) then transfer to baking trays. Re-roll the trimmings and repeat until all dough is used up.","Bake 8-10 minutes (180°C) until lightly golden. Allow to cool on trays for 2 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely. Serve or store in an airtight container."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g caster sugar","1 orange, thin peelings of skin plus 1 Tbsp juice","200 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","140 g unsalted butter, very cold, diced","80 g currants","1 egg yolk, from medium egg"]}],"id":"r86678","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-7X-HJ-Aij5o\/XZWqjH6MrWI\/AAAAAAAAfZk\/sMs8NDbByo4LgjvfyHyIlM3ZTtxg6rfhwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_OhBljkzozssYUFEE.png","title":"Orange Biscuits","publishedAt":"2015-10-19T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0.9 g","fat":"4.4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"10.6 g","calories":"359 kJ \/ 86 kcal"},"usefulItems":"fluted cookie cutter (Ø 6 cm), 2 baking trays and baking paper, cling film, rolling pin, wire rack, airtight container, refrigerator, oven","basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","28 pieces"]}